This article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama designating Memorial Day, May 30, 2011, as a day of prayer for permanent peace. The President also asks all Americans to observe a National Moment of Remembrance at 3:00 p.m. local time on Memorial Day. He requests that flags be flown at half-staff until noon and asks people to display the flag at half-staff from their homes during the forenoon period. The article emphasizes the importance of honoring the brave men and women who have fought and died to defend our freedom and calls on all Americans to come together to strive for a just and lasting peace in the world.